lead_paragraph: Fire crews braced for new troubles today as weather forecasters predicted new Santa Ana winds starting tonight. But they reported substantial progress in containing or dousing most of the major wildfires in Southern California. The National Weather Service issued "red flag" warnings for the entire state of California, predicting 30- to 40-mile-an-hour winds starting tonight and continuing through Saturday.

headline.main: Californians Set For More Wind And New Blazes
